Source: Dictionary of Slang
Author: Partridge
Vol / Page: 280
Edition:
Quote: curly ... Difficult, as in `That's a curly one' ...(?mostly) Aus.: since ca. 11950. ...2. But in NZ as , e.g., `That was extra curly' (Slatter), it seems to mean `excellent' or `attractive' and to date since ca. 1935.
